OL,6,FOutlined in the prosecution, Hicks is
OL,7,Fdescribed as telling the woman he was
OL,8,Fthere to "check her mobility".
OL,10,FAfter she lay down on her bed, the
OL,11,Fwoman says the attacker assaulted her.
OL,13,FWhen she complained, the man
OL,14,Fapologised, telling her he had got
OL,15,F"carried away".
OL,17,FAfter the incident, the elderly woman
OL,18,Fasked the nurse for his identity card,
OL,19,Fwhich he said was in his car. He then
OL,20,Fleft the house.
