OL,6,FHicks suggested it was from the
OL,7,Fprevious meeting, but DNA experts said
OL,8,Fthis was highly unlikely and the
OL,9,Fprosecution says this showed he did
OL,10,Fnot moisturise her in December and the
OL,11,FDNA came from the January assault.
OL,13,FHicks accessed the woman's personal
OL,14,Fdetails on several occasions
OL,15,Fthroughout the two weeks, including
OL,16,Ftwice on the day of the incident even
OL,17,Fwithin the time of his son's visit.
OL,19,FThe prosecution alleged this was so he
OL,20,Fcould find out when she would be alone.
