OL,6,F"He's his own person, confident in
OL,7,Fwhat he says. There are parts of his
OL,8,Faccount in court that differed from
OL,9,Fpolice interview, and he says that's
OL,10,Fbecause he couldn't remember.
OL,12,F"As the prosecution case would say,
OL,13,Fit's because it's untrue."
OL,15,FOn remembering minute details of his
OL,16,Ffirst visit to the victim, versus
OL,17,Fhaving no memory of his whereabouts at
OL,18,Fthe time of the incident, Sharman says
OL,19,Fit's a way for him to get out by
OL,20,Fsaying he was there.
