OL,6,FShilpa Shah, Crown Prosecution Service
OL,7,Flawyer, said: "This was a shocking
OL,8,Fcrime carried out by someone in a
OL,9,Ftrusted profession.
OL,11,F"Steven Hicks knew the victim was
OL,12,Fvulnerable and that no other carers
OL,13,Fwere due to visit her that evening,
OL,14,Fand he used his position to gain
OL,15,Faccess to her home to assault her, in
OL,16,Fher own bedroom.
OL,18,F"Hicks denied the charges against him,
OL,19,Fbut we were able to present evidence
OL,20,Fto the court clearly linking him to
OL,21,Fthe assault.
